sentences: Sunday Shipushu (born 13 March 1983), known as Sunny Boy is a Namibian rapper from Ongwediva.
He rose to fame after collaborating with Gazza on his song "Koko" in 2004.
He increased his buzz with his hit single "Balance" in 2005 when he signed with Mshasho Productions.

In 2011 Sunny Boy changed managers from his sister Cathy Shipushu, who has been his managers since the establishment of Yaziza Entertainment, to Mercy Hoabes.
Sunny Boy was first heard on Gazza's hit song "Koko" in 2004, which developed the duo into a good relationship.
In 2008 he released a hip hop track titled "Intro" off his third album, where he called Gazza out.
In 2009, Gazza's crew StreetKids dissed Sunny on their song "Who's Fooling Who".

Sunday Shipushu (born 13 March 1983), known as Sunny Boy is a Namibian rapper from Ongwediva.
Sunny Boy was born, Pendukeni Andreas Sunday Shipushu, in Oshakati, a town in northern Namibia, and grew up in its neighbour Ongwediva.
Even then, they dreamed of one day making it big in the music industry.
In September 2006, Sunny Boy left Mshasho Records, and launched his own record label, GreenHouse Entertainment (now Yaziza Entertainment).
